    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-28T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.76/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-28T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 28, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 28—3:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. My 38, May 21, 1 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d106fn32">Not printed.</note> This
                    morning’s papers announcing signature of the contract yesterday, I saw the
                    Minister of Communications who confirmed it. Upon my expressing my regret that
                    Durham had not been given an opportunity to make his explanations before the
                    committee, Minister replied that nothing that Durham could have said could have
                    influenced the result.</p>
                <pb facs="0232" n="114" xml:id="pg_114"/>
                <p>I believe that considerations other than technical have been decisive. Mr.
                    Venizelos by the mere expression of his wish could have secured the necessary
                    hearing for Mr. Durham. It may be that he wants to give this contract to a
                    British firm by way of showing that he is not actuated by anti-British sentiment
                    as he has often been lately accused of being.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
